# BLS / ACLS / PALS emergency readiness (future pathways)

When implementing **BLS, ACLS, PALS**, or adjacent certification readiness:

- Position as **adaptive clinical readiness + emergency-response ecosystems** inside the NurseNest subscription — **not** isolated certification courses, CE portals, LMS silos, or watch-and-quiz utilities.

## Integrate

- **ECG + telemetry** infrastructure — algorithms and rhythms as **teaching arcs**, not a second ECG product (`docs/ecg-module-integration.md`).
- **Labs + med calc** — electrolytes, ABGs, emergency meds, titration, pediatric dosing via existing `/app/labs` and `/app/med-calculations` patterns.
- **OSCE** — rapid response, code communication, escalation — shared scenario shells.
- **Branching cases** — arrest, deterioration, pediatric emergencies — `adaptive-case-study-ecosystem.md`.
- **Dashboard / report** — extend mastery and adaptive remediation on **`/app/account/report`** — no parallel cert dashboard.

## Themes + Figma

Same shells and tokens; Midnight may emphasize immersive ICU/ER — **expression only**, no layout fork per theme.

